---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Trust center" description="Security posture, planned audits, and transparency.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold">Trust center</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">
      Honest disclosure of the project's current security posture. HelixGitpx is
      open source (Apache-2.0 / CC-BY-SA-4.0); there is no hosted Service yet.
      This page describes what a future hosted operator can offer, plus what the
      project ships by default for self-hosters.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/security" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6 hover:border-primary">
        <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500">Built in</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold">Security posture</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">TLS, mTLS via SPIFFE, OPA authorization, signed SBOMs, supply-chain CI.</div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/HelixDevelopment/HelixGitpx/blob/main/docs/UNFINISHED.md"
         class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6 hover:border-primary">
        <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500">Disclosure</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold">What's not yet done</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Living inventory of every gap, with reasons.</div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold">Compliance posture</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">No active certifications. The project ships the technical controls and the evidence-collection tooling so an operator of a hosted Service can pursue audits on their own timeline.</p>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
      <li><span class="inline-block w-28 text-sm text-slate-500">SOC 2</span> Evidence mapping committed under <code>docs/security/soc2-type1-evidence-index.md</code>. No report has been issued; no auditor engaged.</li>
      <li><span class="inline-block w-28 text-sm text-slate-500">ISO 27001</span> Gap analysis committed under <code>docs/security/iso27001-gap-analysis.md</code>. No certification in progress.</li>
      <li><span class="inline-block w-28 text-sm text-slate-500">Pen-test</span> Scope document committed under <code>docs/security/pentest-scope-2026q2.md</code>. No vendor engaged; no test conducted.</li>
      <li><span class="inline-block w-28 text-sm text-slate-500">Bug bounty</span> Program rules committed under <code>docs/security/bug-bounty-program.md</code>. Not yet live on any platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold">Sub-processors</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">None — there is no hosted Service. The <a href="/subprocessors" class="text-primary hover:underline">subprocessors page</a> is a template for future operators.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold">Data residency (self-hosted)</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">Per-org residency is an implemented feature (<code>org.organizations.residency</code> column + <code>SetOrgResidency</code> RPC). Your data stays wherever you run the cluster; there is no HelixGitpx cloud today.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold">Report a vulnerability</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Open a security advisory on
      <a href="https://github.com/HelixDevelopment/HelixGitpx/security/advisories" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub</a>
      or email the maintainer (see the GitHub profile). There is no public
      bug-bounty program yet; when a hosted Service launches, this page
      will link to the HackerOne program at that point.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
